-1939345857.text: "In determining the phosphorylation status of S6K1 at T389 [pS6K1 (T389)] and 4EBP1 at S65 [p4EBP1 (S65)], which are two downstream phosphorylation sites of mTOR, we found higher expression of pS6K1 (T389) and p4EBP1 (S65) in 453-TSC1 (SSDD) stable transfectants than in MDA-MB-453-TSC1 (WT) or MDA-MB-453- TSC1 (SSAA) stable transfectants (XREF_FIG), confirming our previous finding that IKKbeta phosphorylation of TSC1 activates the mTOR pathway."
